The CCTO powder was prepared to employ an oxalate precursor route. The material obtained was earth brown. XRD characterization was conducted to obtain the material's crystal structure and phase composition, as shown in Fig. 1. The XRD patterns were obtained on the as-prepared CCTO catalyst shown in the Fig. 1a perfectly matching the ICDD data no. 01-075-1149 displayed in Fig. 1b. The results state the single-phase nature of the CCTO sample as there are no residual peaks of CuO and TiO2 using this synthesis route. The crystallite size for CCTO was calculated to be 26 nm employing the Scherrer formula:1D=Kλβcosθ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
